## Right-to-left(rtl) support

React native supports RTL languages. The best way to access RTL mode is via the `I18nManager`.

### I18nManager

#### I18nManager.isRTL()
Getter, Returns boolean
Checks if user's device is RTL

```
const IS_RTL = I18nManager.isRTL();
```

#### I18nManager.allowRTL();
Setter
If true, If IS_RTL is `true` will change app layout to RTL
If false, will disable RTL layout

```
const I18nManager.allowRTL(true); // 
```

I18nManager.forceRTL(true);
Setter
If true, and even if user's device isn't RTL, will force app to use RTL layout

```
const I18nManager.forceRTL(true); // 
```


### Notes for implementation
Keep in mind that when you use RTL layout, all components will flip horizontally. 
For instance and as confusing it might sound, in order to make the a `<Text>` component right-aligned we will use `textAlign: 'left'` and vice versa.
